  "severity": "None",
  "overview": "An update for libvirt is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.",
  "description": "Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM) offers a full virtualization solution forLinux on numerous hardware platforms. The virt:rhel module contains packageswhich provide user-space components used to run virtual machines using KVM.The packages also provide APIs for managing and interacting with the virtualized systems.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): RFE: provide a way to override QEMU crypto priority for live migration [rhel-9.6.z] (JIRA:RHEL-106277)  libvirt report unexpected warning about shared memory in the log [rhel-9] (JIRA:RHEL-106504)",
